  "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nI am using geth as a library (version: 1.8.8) and running nodes on a (private) Clique network.\r\n\r\nWhether running these nodes on my MBP OSX (High Sierra) or on Ubuntu VMs, I get 100 % CPU load, even after the network is synced.\r\n\r\nProfiling for 120 seconds on OSX, I see that this linked to the call to `rand` reader in `querySeeds`, see this (compressed) SVG  file below [geth.cpu.svg.zip](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/files/2101983/geth.cpu.svg.zip)\r\n\r\nThis problem is also clearly visible on the CPU load of the Linux VMs where the entropy daemon `haveged` is under heavy load\r\n\r\n<img width=\"301\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/797684/41408463-1382a3c6-6fd3-11e8-9bfa-eb441e5c8d21.png\">\r\n\r\nAny idea where this is coming from and what I can do about it ?\r\n\r\nb.\r\n",
