    "body": "Digging a bit in this\r\n\r\nThe infinite `for` loop in `discv5#loop()` does a select on channel `refreshDone`\r\n\r\n```go\r\n\t\tcase <-refreshDone:\r\n\t\t\tlog.Trace(\"<-net.refreshDone\", \"table size\", net.tab.count)\r\n\t\t\tif net.tab.count != 0 {\r\n                           ...\r\n\t\t\t} else {\r\n\t\t\t\trefreshDone = make(chan struct{})\r\n\t\t\t\tnet.refresh(refreshDone)\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n```\r\nThe table being empty `net.refresh()` is called which in turns calls `querySeeds`\r\n\r\n```go\r\n\r\nfunc (net *Network) refresh(done chan<- struct{}) {\r\n\tvar seeds []*Node\r\n\tif net.db != nil {\r\n\t\tseeds = net.db.querySeeds(seedCount, seedMaxAge)\r\n\t}\r\n\tif len(seeds) == 0 {\r\n\t\tseeds = net.nursery\r\n\t}\r\n\tif len(seeds) == 0 {\r\n\t\tlog.Trace(\"no seed nodes found\")\r\n\t\tclose(done)\r\n\t\treturn\r\n\t}\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\nSince no seeds are found, the channel `refreshDone` is closed and the loop in `discv5#loop()` spins continuously at maximum CPU.\r\n\r\nBeing on a private network with a limited numbers of nodes \"bootstrapped\" with a list in static-nodes.json, the node is unlikely to find any seed and this loop will run at max CPU continuously.\r\n\r\n1. Apart for deactivating discovery V5 - which I would like to avoid  - what other options do I have ?\r\n2. More generally, having this loop run continuously without a timer to spin the wheel a bit between runs, seems pretty harsh .. or did I miss something ?\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
